# Web React Rules

Keep HTTP access in `apps/web/src/api` and route it through `apiFetch`. Components should call typed API helpers rather than constructing fetch requests inline.

Use `@boardgame/shared` response and payload types for API data. Do not duplicate backend DTOs in the web app.

Keep React Query keys centralized in `apps/web/src/lib/query-keys.ts` when adding or changing server state.

Prefer derived state over duplicated local state. Store only user input or UI state locally.

Components should stay focused on rendering and interaction. Extract reusable UI into `components/ui` and reusable feature logic into hooks or `lib` helpers when it is used in more than one place.

Handle loading, empty, and error states deliberately for user-facing data. Do not leave failed requests invisible.

Avoid unsafe casts around route params, API responses, and form values. Parse or narrow values before using them.
